Here's how to cover all three requirements:

### 1. Detect the current system theme

```csharp
AppTheme current = Application.Current!.RequestedTheme;
// AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified
```

### 2. Subscribe to real-time theme changes

```csharp
// In your App constructor or wherever appropriate:
Application.Current!.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {e.RequestedTheme}");
    // Update UI, swap ResourceDictionaries, etc.
};
```

### 3. Force a specific theme (ignore system setting)

```csharp
// Force dark mode
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Reset to follow the system
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

Persist the user's choice across launches:

```csharp
// Save
Preferences.Set("AppTheme", "Dark");

// Restore on startup
var saved = Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "System");
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = saved switch
{
    "Light" => AppTheme.Light,
    "Dark"  => AppTheme.Dark,
    _       => AppTheme.Unspecified
};
```

### ⚠️ Critical Android pitfall

Your `MainActivity` **must** include `ConfigChanges.UiMode` or theme-change events won't fire (the activity restarts instead):

```csharp
[Activity(Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
          MainLauncher = true,
          ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
                               | ConfigChanges.Orientation
                               | ConfigChanges.UiMode  // ← Required
                               | ConfigChanges.ScreenLayout
                               | ConfigChanges.SmallestScreenSize
                               | ConfigChanges.Density)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

### Theme-aware XAML

Use `AppThemeBinding` for automatic light/dark switching, or `DynamicResource` if you swap full `ResourceDictionary` files at runtime:

```xml
<!-- Simple approach -->
<Label TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Green, Dark=Red}" />

<!-- ResourceDictionary approach (supports runtime swapping) -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

> **Key rule:** always use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) when swapping dictionaries — `StaticResource` freezes at first load.
